# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Agent Instructions

The engineering rules for this repo live in **[CLAUDE.md](./CLAUDE.md)** — that is
the single source of truth. Read it.

`AGENTS.md` exists because different AI coding CLIs look for different filenames
(Claude Code reads `CLAUDE.md`; Codex, Gemini, and others read `AGENTS.md`). Rather
than maintain two copies that drift apart, this file is a thin pointer.

**Keep it DRY — pick ONE canonical file:**

- If most of your agents read `CLAUDE.md`, keep the full rules there and leave this
  pointer as-is.
- If most read `AGENTS.md`, move the full rules here and make `CLAUDE.md` the thin
  pointer instead.

Either way, never let the two files contain *different* rules — a contradiction
between them is worse than either rule alone.

> Tip: on systems that support it, symlink one to the other
> (`ln -s CLAUDE.md AGENTS.md`) so there is physically one file.
